analysis: The documents primarily concern the withdrawal, reservation, or modification of public lands for various federal uses. These uses include wildlife refuges, military purposes (antiaircraft firing ranges, target ranges, naval aviation), forest service needs (lookout stations, ranger stations, road construction), flood control, water sources, soil erosion control, and air navigation facilities. Many of the orders either establish these reservations or modify/revoke previous orders related to them. The documents frequently cite the Act of June 25, 1910, as amended, as the legal basis for these actions.
title: Federal Land Reservations and Withdrawals
